# Step 4: Deploy Command

**Phase:** 9 -- CLI Tool
**Step:** 4 of 7
**Status:** Not Started
**Depends on:** Step 1 (CLI API route `POST /api/cli/deploy`), Step 2 (Login), Step 3 (Link), Phase 8 (Build log streaming via WebSocket/SSE)
**Depends on this step:** None (independent of Steps 5-7)

---

## Goal

Implement `gblockparty deploy` so the user can trigger a deployment from the terminal. The command reads the linked project config and current git info, sends a deploy request to the API, streams build logs in real-time, and prints the deployment URL on success.

---

## Background

The deploy command is the most complex CLI command. It needs to:

1. Read the linked project ID from `.gblockparty/config.json`
2. Detect the current git branch and commit SHA from the local repository
3. Send a `POST /api/cli/deploy` request with the project ID, branch, commit SHA, and production flag
4. Connect to the returned `streamUrl` to receive build logs in real-time
5. Display logs with proper ANSI color support
6. Show a final success or failure message with the deployment URL

---

## File to Modify

### `packages/cli/src/commands/deploy.ts`

**Current state:** Prints "Deploy not yet implemented". Has `--branch` option defined.

**Target implementation:**

```typescript
import { Command } from "commander";
import chalk from "chalk";
import ora from "ora";
import { execSync } from "node:child_process";
import { ApiClient } from "../lib/api-client";
import { getGlobalConfig, getProjectConfig } from "../lib/config";

interface DeployResponse {
  deploymentId: string;
  type: string;
  branch: string;
  streamUrl: string;
}

interface DeploymentResult {
  id: string;
  status: string;
  url?: string;
  errorMessage?: string;
}

export const deployCommand = new Command("deploy")
  .description("Trigger a deployment")
  .option("--prod", "Deploy to production")
  .option("-b, --branch <branch>", "Branch to deploy")
  .action(async (options: { prod?: boolean; branch?: string }) => {
    // Check authentication
    const config = getGlobalConfig();
    if (!config.token) {
      console.error(chalk.red("Not authenticated. Run `gblockparty login` first."));
      process.exit(1);
    }

    // Check project link
    const projectConfig = getProjectConfig();
    if (!projectConfig) {
      console.error(chalk.red("No project linked. Run `gblockparty link` first."));
      process.exit(1);
    }

    // Detect git info
    const branch = options.branch ?? getGitBranch();
    const commitSha = getGitCommitSha();

    if (!branch) {
      console.error(chalk.red("Could not detect git branch. Use --branch to specify."));
      process.exit(1);
    }

    const deployType = options.prod ? "production" : "preview";
    console.log(chalk.dim(`Deploying ${chalk.bold(branch)} (${commitSha?.slice(0, 7) ?? "latest"}) as ${deployType}...`));

    // Trigger deployment
    const spinner = ora("Triggering deployment...").start();
    const client = new ApiClient();

    let deployResponse: DeployResponse;
    try {
      deployResponse = await client.post<DeployResponse>("/api/cli/deploy", {
        projectId: projectConfig.projectId,
        branch,
        commitSha,
        production: options.prod ?? false,
      });
      spinner.succeed(`Deployment queued (${deployResponse.deploymentId.slice(0, 8)})`);
    } catch (error) {
      spinner.fail(chalk.red("Failed to trigger deployment"));
      if (error instanceof Error) {
        console.error(chalk.red(error.message));
      }
      process.exit(1);
    }

    // Stream build logs
    console.log(chalk.dim("\n--- Build Logs ---\n"));

    try {
      await streamBuildLogs(config, deployResponse.streamUrl);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(chalk.yellow("\nLog streaming interrupted."));
      console.error(chalk.dim("The deployment may still be running."));
    }

    // Fetch final deployment status
    const statusSpinner = ora("Checking deployment status...").start();
    try {
      const result = await client.get<DeploymentResult>(
        `/api/projects/${projectConfig.projectId}/deployments/${deployResponse.deploymentId}`
      );

      if (result.status === "ready") {
        statusSpinner.succeed(chalk.green("Deployment successful!"));
        if (result.url) {
          console.log(chalk.green(`\n  ${chalk.bold(result.url)}\n`));
        }
      } else if (result.status === "failed") {
        statusSpinner.fail(chalk.red("Deployment failed"));
        if (result.errorMessage) {
          console.error(chalk.red(result.errorMessage));
        }
        process.exit(1);
      } else {
        statusSpinner.info(chalk.yellow(`Deployment status: ${result.status}`));
        console.log(chalk.dim("Check the dashboard for more details."));
      }
    } catch (error) {
      statusSpinner.fail(chalk.yellow("Could not fetch deployment status"));
      console.log(chalk.dim("Check the dashboard for deployment results."));
    }
  });

function getGitBranch(): string | null {
  try {
    return execSync("git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD", { encoding: "utf-8" }).trim();
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}

function getGitCommitSha(): string | null {
  try {
    return execSync("git rev-parse HEAD", { encoding: "utf-8" }).trim();
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}

async function streamBuildLogs(
  config: { apiUrl?: string; token?: string },
  streamUrl: string
): Promise<void> {
  const apiUrl = config.apiUrl ?? "http://localhost:3000";
  const fullUrl = `${apiUrl}${streamUrl}`;

  // Option A: WebSocket streaming
  // const ws = new WebSocket(fullUrl, {
  //   headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${config.token}` },
  // });
  //
  // return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  //   ws.on("message", (data) => {
  //     process.stdout.write(data.toString());
  //   });
  //   ws.on("close", () => resolve());
  //   ws.on("error", (err) => reject(err));
  // });

  // Option B: SSE streaming (EventSource)
  // Use fetch with streaming response
  const response = await fetch(fullUrl, {
    headers: {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${config.token}`,
      Accept: "text/event-stream",
    },
  });

  if (!response.ok) {
    throw new Error(`Stream error: ${response.status}`);
  }

  const reader = response.body?.getReader();
  if (!reader) {
    throw new Error("No response body");
  }

  const decoder = new TextDecoder();
  while (true) {
    const { done, value } = await reader.read();
    if (done) break;
    const chunk = decoder.decode(value, { stream: true });

    // Parse SSE events
    const lines = chunk.split("\n");
    for (const line of lines) {
      if (line.startsWith("data: ")) {
        const data = line.slice(6);
        if (data === "[DONE]") return;
        process.stdout.write(data + "\n");
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Git Info Detection

The command detects the current git branch and commit SHA using `git rev-parse`:

- **Branch**: `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD` returns the current branch name (e.g., `main`, `feature/new-thing`)
- **Commit SHA**: `git rev-parse HEAD` returns the full 40-character commit SHA

Both are wrapped in try/catch blocks. If git is not available or the directory is not a git repository, the branch can be specified manually via `--branch`.

---

## Build Log Streaming

The `streamUrl` returned by `POST /api/cli/deploy` points to a WebSocket or SSE endpoint that streams build log lines in real-time. The implementation should support both protocols, preferring SSE for simplicity (one-way streaming is sufficient for logs).

**SSE format:**
```
data: Installing dependencies...
data: added 1423 packages in 12s
data: Building project...
data: [DONE]
```

The `[DONE]` sentinel indicates the stream has completed. The CLI should stop reading and check the final deployment status.

**Log output rules:**
- ANSI escape codes are preserved (build tools emit colored output)
- Each `data:` line is written directly to stdout
- No additional formatting is applied to log lines (they appear exactly as the build process outputs them)

---

## Command Flags

| Flag | Short | Description | Default |
|------|-------|-------------|---------|
| `--prod` | none | Deploy to production | `false` (preview deployment) |
| `--branch` | `-b` | Override the detected git branch | Auto-detected from git |

---

## Output Format

**During deployment:**
```
Deploying main (a1b2c3d) as production...
✔ Deployment queued (550e8400)

--- Build Logs ---

Cloning repository...
Installing dependencies...
added 1423 packages in 12s
Building project...
Creating optimized production build...
✓ Compiled successfully
Building Docker image...
Image built: myapp:a1b2c3d4 (145 MB)
Starting container...
Health check passed

✔ Deployment successful!

  https://myapp.yourdomain.dev
```

**On failure:**
```
Deploying main (a1b2c3d) as production...
✔ Deployment queued (550e8400)

--- Build Logs ---

Cloning repository...
Installing dependencies...
Building project...
Error: Module not found: 'missing-package'

✖ Deployment failed
Build error: Module not found: 'missing-package'
```

---

## Edge Cases

| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Not authenticated | Print auth error, exit with code 1 |
| Not linked to a project | Print link error, exit with code 1 |
| Not in a git repository | Print error; allow `--branch` override but no commit SHA |
| API returns 404 (project deleted) | Print "Project not found" error, exit with code 1 |
| Build log stream drops | Print warning "Log streaming interrupted", check final status |
| Deployment times out | After stream ends, poll for final status; print status or "check dashboard" |
| `--prod` flag with dirty working tree | No warning (deployment uses the committed code on the server, not local files) |

